o4-mini Answer:
First rewrite as one radical and simplify inside:

\[
\frac{\sqrt{50\,s^3}}{\sqrt{128\,s}}
=\sqrt{\frac{50\,s^3}{128\,s}}
=\sqrt{\frac{50}{128}\,s^2}
=\sqrt{\frac{25}{64}\,s^2}
=\frac{5}{8}\,\sqrt{s^2}
=\frac{5}{8}\,\lvert s\rvert.
\]

Since under the roots we require \(s\ge0\), \(\lvert s\rvert=s\) and the result is

\[
\boxed{\frac{5s}{8}}.
\]

First factor under each radical:

\[
\frac{\sqrt{162\,x^{10}y^2}}{\sqrt{2\,x^6y^6}}
=\frac{\sqrt{81\cdot2\;x^{10}\;y^2}}{\sqrt{2\;x^6\;y^6}}
=\frac{9\,x^5\,y\,\sqrt2}{x^3\,y^3\,\sqrt2}
=9\,x^{5-3}\,y^{1-3}
=9\,\frac{x^2}{y^2}.
\]

To rationalize the denominator, multiply numerator and denominator by √5:

\[
\frac{6}{\sqrt{5}}
\;\times\;
\frac{\sqrt{5}}{\sqrt{5}}
\;=\;
\frac{6\sqrt{5}}{5}.
\]

To simplify \(\frac{5}{2\sqrt{5}}\), multiply top and bottom by \(\sqrt{5}$\) to rationalize the denominator:

\[
\frac{5}{2\sqrt{5}}\;\times\;\frac{\sqrt{5}}{\sqrt{5}}
\;=\;\frac{5\sqrt{5}}{2\cdot 5}
\;=\;\frac{\sqrt{5}}{2}.
\]

To simplify \(-\frac{9}{4\sqrt3}\), multiply top and bottom by \(\sqrt3\) to rationalize the denominator:

\[
-\frac{9}{4\sqrt3}\;\times\;\frac{\sqrt3}{\sqrt3}
\;=\;
-\frac{9\sqrt3}{4\cdot3}
\;=\;
-\frac{9\sqrt3}{12}
\;=\;
-\frac{3\sqrt3}{4}.
\]

So the simplified form is \(-\tfrac{3\sqrt3}{4}\).

To simplify \(\frac{2}{2+\sqrt3}\), multiply top and bottom by the conjugate \(2-\sqrt3\):

\[
\frac{2}{2+\sqrt3}\cdot\frac{2-\sqrt3}{2-\sqrt3}
=\frac{2(2-\sqrt3)}{(2+\sqrt3)(2-\sqrt3)}
=\frac{4-2\sqrt3}{4-3}
=4-2\sqrt3.
\]

To rationalize the denominator multiply top and bottom by \(5-\sqrt3\):  
\[
\frac{5}{5+\sqrt3}\;\times\;\frac{5-\sqrt3}{5-\sqrt3}
=\frac{5(5-\sqrt3)}{(5+\sqrt3)(5-\sqrt3)}
=\frac{25-5\sqrt3}{25-3}
=\frac{25-5\sqrt3}{22}
=\frac{5(5-\sqrt3)}{22}\,. 
\]

To rationalize the denominator, multiply top and bottom by the conjugate of \(4-\sqrt6\), which is \(4+\sqrt6\):

\[
\frac{2}{4-\sqrt6}
\;=\;
\frac{2}{4-\sqrt6}\cdot\frac{4+\sqrt6}{4+\sqrt6}
\;=\;
\frac{2(4+\sqrt6)}{(4)^2-(\sqrt6)^2}
\;=\;
\frac{2(4+\sqrt6)}{16-6}
\;=\;
\frac{2(4+\sqrt6)}{10}
\;=\;
\frac{4+\sqrt6}{5}.
\]

To rationalize the denominator, multiply top and bottom by the conjugate \(\sqrt{x}-\sqrt{2}\):

\[
\frac{\sqrt{5}}{\sqrt{x}+\sqrt{2}}
\;\times\;
\frac{\sqrt{x}-\sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{x}-\sqrt{2}}
=
\frac{\sqrt{5}\,(\sqrt{x}-\sqrt{2})}{(\sqrt{x}+\sqrt{2})(\sqrt{x}-\sqrt{2})}
=\frac{\sqrt{5x}-\sqrt{10}}{x-2}\,.
\]

So the simplified form is
\[
\boxed{\frac{\sqrt{5x}-\sqrt{10}}{x-2}}\quad(x>0,\;x\neq2).
\]

To rationalize the denominator, multiply top and bottom by the conjugate \(\sqrt y+\sqrt3\):

\[
\frac{\sqrt{10}}{\sqrt y-\sqrt3}
\;\times\;
\frac{\sqrt y+\sqrt3}{\sqrt y+\sqrt3}
\;=\;
\frac{\sqrt{10}\,(\sqrt y+\sqrt3)}{(\sqrt y)^2-(\sqrt3)^2}
\;=\;
\frac{\sqrt{10y}+\sqrt{30}}{y-3}.
\]

o3 Answer:
To remove the radical from the denominator, multiply by the conjugate of the denominator, √q – √10:

\[
\frac{\sqrt{q} - \sqrt{10}}{\sqrt{q} + \sqrt{10}}
\;
\cdot
\;
\frac{\sqrt{q} - \sqrt{10}}{\sqrt{q} - \sqrt{10}}
\]

Numerator:

\[
(\sqrt{q}-\sqrt{10})^{2}
= (\sqrt{q})^{2}-2\sqrt{q}\sqrt{10}+(\sqrt{10})^{2}
= q - 2\sqrt{10q} + 10
\]

Denominator (difference of squares):

\[
(\sqrt{q}+\sqrt{10})(\sqrt{q}-\sqrt{10})=(\sqrt{q})^{2}-(\sqrt{10})^{2}=q-10
\]

Hence

\[
\frac{\sqrt{q} - \sqrt{10}}{\sqrt{q} + \sqrt{10}}
=
\frac{q + 10 - 2\sqrt{10q}}{\,q - 10}
\;=\;
\frac{(\sqrt{q}-\sqrt{10})^{2}}{q-10}.
\]

Either form is an acceptable rationalized (simplified) result.
